8 PROPOSED POLICY COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
9 An Act relating to game and fish; amending 29 O.S.
2021, Section 5-102, which relates to tagging of
10 wildlife; exempting tag fee for tags for certain
animals; and providing an effective date.
11
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 29 O.S. 2021, Section 5-102, is
16 amended to read as follows:
17 Section 5-102. A. No person may remove any propagated or
18 released wildlife or domesticated animals hunted for sport which are
19 killed at a commercial hunting area, including exotic wildlife,
20 without attaching a tag to each of such killed wildlife or
21 domesticated animals hunted for sport.
22 B. The tags shall be supplied by the Commission at a cost of no
23 more than Ten Dollars ($10.00); provided, that there shall be no fee
24 for tags for females of the Cervidae family, feral swine, exotic
Req. No. 15994 Page 1

1 wild life not native to North America, which are hunted for sport and
2 killed at a commercial hunting area. The tags shall contain such
3 information as the Commission may require and shall be numbered
4 consecutively.
5 C. Such tag must remain attached to the individual wildlife or
6 domesticated animals hunted for sport until prepared and consumed
7 and shall not be used more than once.
8 D. Any person convicted of violating the provisions of this
9 section shall be punished by a fine of not less than One Hundred
10 Dollars ($100.00) nor more than Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00), or
11 by imprisonment in the county jail not to exceed sixty (60) days, or
12 by both such fine and imprisonment.
13 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
